==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Cassius
<hw>Cas"sius</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From the name of the
discoverer, A. <etsep>Cassius</etsep>, a German physician of the 17th
centry.]</ety> <def>A brownish purple pigment, obtained by the action of
some compounds of tin upon certain salts of gold. It is used in painting
and staining porcelain and glass to give a beautiful purple color.
Commonly called <altname>Purple of Cassius</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cassock</ent>⟦br⟧
